# Character System Blueprint: Corey (The Baseline)
**Design Philosophy:** Frictionless, scalable, and high-velocity. No complex button combos. Inputs are mapped strictly by player intent, segregating the controller into left-side movement/utility and right-side combat/violence.

---

## 1. Ergonomic Control Architecture

| Button | Left Side (Movement & Forms) | Right Side (Combat & Ordinance) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Bumper (1)** | **L1:** Jet Sprint (Tap for 3s speed burst) | **R1:** Sledge Parry (Tap) / Emergency Block (Hold) |
| **Trigger (2)** | **L2:** Asset Morph (Tap) / Sniper Bullet-Time (Hold) | **R2:** Fire Active Gun Mode |
| **Face Buttons**| **Left Stick:** Physics & Vector Direction | **Square:** Hazmat Grenade Deployment<br>**Triangle:** Contextual Heavy (Distance = Rocket / Melee = Vault)<br>**Circle:** Grapnel Winch (Pull / Armor Strip)<br>**Cross:** Aerial Hover Jets |
| **Stick Clicks**| **L3 + R3:** Overclocked Reaper Mode (Super State) | **Right Stick (Flick):** Elemental Quadrant Selection |

