## 2. Core Gear & Direct Asset Morphing

### A. The Chimaera Frame (Primary Firearm)
No UI menus or weapon wheels. Tapping or holding L2 physically morphs the singular weapon actor model in real-time to signal state changes.

*   **State 1: Dual Pistols (Default Ground State)**
    *   Input: Tap L2 to ensure weapon is separated. Tap R2 to fire.
    *   Role: High fire-rate, low recoil. Serves as her primary ground combo-builder to skyrocket the hit counter and chip light enemies.
*   **State 2: Frontal Cone Shotgun (Ground Utility)**
    *   Input: Tap L2 to collapse the pistols into a single chassis. Tap R2 to fire.
    *   Role: Delivers a massive, wide-angle kinetic blast with severe pushback against light and medium anomalies to clear space.
*   **State 3: Anti-Material Sniper Rifle (Aerial Execution)**
    *   Input: Hold L2 (Anywhere state). 
    *   Role: Automatically engages over-the-shoulder manual aiming. If activated airborne, it triggers localized bullet-time, morphing the gun into a heavy, extended-barrel anti-materiel cannon to target exposed anomaly weak points.

### B. The Sledge Rig (Forearm Exoskeleton Framework)
An industrial, company-issued skeletal sleeve running along her arm. It handles extreme physical stress, heavy payload distribution, and physics redirection.

*   **The Jet-Boosted Parry (Tap R1):** A high-skill-ceiling defensive swing. Uses back-jet acceleration to snap the armored forearm frame across her body to violently stagger incoming attacks.
*   **Emergency Block (Hold R1):** A panic-mitigation tool. Locks the hydraulics into a rigid guard. Discouraged via a resource penalty (heavy stamina/fuel drain or accumulating post-run repair costs).
*   **Grapnel Winch (Circle):** Dual-purpose high-tension line. Pulls her to geometry, or clamps onto heavy anomaly armor plates to mechanically rip them off.
*   **Contextual Heavy Payload (Triangle):** 
    *   Ranged Distance: Fires a straight-line heavy explosive rocket.
    *   Melee Distance (Context Sensitive): Instantly triggers the Melee Vault. Drives the rig blade into the anomaly, uses forward momentum to pole-vault over its head, and automatically fires the rocket downward to launch Corey into sky-high orbit.

